      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/130/5609",
      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ مَاتَ وَ تَرَكَ اِبْنَتَهُ وَ أُخْتَهُ لِأَبِيهِ وَ أُمِّهِ فَقَالَ \"اَلْمَالُ لِلاِبْنَةِ وَ لَيْسَ لِلْأُخْتِ مِنَ اَلْأَبِ وَ اَلْأُمِّ شَيْءٌ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5609 - It is narrated by Al-Hasan ibn Mahbub from Ali ibn Ri'ab from Zurara from Abu Jafar Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) regarding a man who passed away and left behind his daughter and his full sister (sister from his father and mother).\nImam (as) said: \"The wealth belongs to the daughter, and the full sister has no share in it.\""
        ]
      }
    },
